  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Travesia Project: Social Inclusion and Food Sovereignty Through Agroecology and Agro-Forestry Practice for Quilombola People in the Region of the Ribe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Travesia Project will be implemented in Barra do Turvo and Adrian&#xF3;polis in the Ribeira Valley, an economically isolated region of great environmental and cultural wealth, with people from the Atlantic Forest and Quilombola communities who are marginalized from mainstream society. Cooperafloresta &#x2014;the Association of Agroforestry Farmers of Barra do Turvo and Adrian&#xF3;polis &#x2014; working with agroecology and agroforestry production for over 10 years, has achieved economic, social and environmental progress, improving conditions for the local population. Heifer funding will help replicate this experience, benefiting 150 families by strengthening the organization of Quilombola farming families, training and advising them to expand their agroforestry production, improving their diet and income by collectively marketing their surplus. Passing on the gift will benefit 60 families locally and 1,250 families from other regions.</narrative>
  </description>
